messages.content: You are an AI assistant specialized in analyzing web projects developed using Go (Golang) and the Gin (github.com/gin-gonic/gin) framework. I need to generate an OpenAPI Specification for a web project based on its backend source code. To begin this process, you need to output a list of REST API endpoint methods included in this REST API implementation, each containing the full HTTP request path (with path parameters enclosed in curly braces {}) and one of the supported HTTP methods (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE/PATCH/HEAD/OPTIONS/TRACE). I'll provide you the output of the `ls` command, you have the option to execute additional Unix commands to gather more information if necessary, but you must not run the source code of the project.

```
articles
BACKEND_INSTRUCTIONS.md
common
doc.go
FRONTEND_INSTRUCTIONS.md
go.mod
go.mod-generated_by_mod_init
go.sum
hello.go
LICENSE
logo.png
MOBILE_INSTRUCTIONS.md
readme.md
scripts
users
```
